    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60d31/76 supp.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Albright</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-06T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 6, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Department’s No. 20, July 19, 1934, 7 p.m. The Finnish Legation at Washington
                    has not been able to obtain a reply from the Finnish Foreign Office with respect
                    to our proposal for exploratory conversations.</p>
                <p>Please consult Mr. Sayre, who will arrive at Helsingfors on the steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Scan-Penn</hi> on August 7, and, if it meets with his
                    approval, make appropriate inquiries of the Foreign Office and indicate our <pb
                        facs="0245" n="145" xml:id="pg_145"/> interest in receiving an early
                    acceptance from the Finnish Government so that the necessary preliminary studies
                    may be undertaken at once.</p>
                <p>Telegraph action taken and results.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
